images.title: The Garden of Europe
images.caption: In the Garden of Europe
images.desc: Welcome to the Garden of Europe - a nickname given to this flower garden in Lisse, Netherlands. The literal translation of Keukenhof, from Dutch to English, is ‘kitchen court’, as the original grounds were a vegetable garden for the royal residents of Keuken Castle during the 15th century.
